III. PROJECT RENAMING OBLIGATION (MANDATORY)

When you distribute a modified version of the Software as a STANDALONE PROJECT,
you MUST rename the project to a name that is CLEARLY DIFFERENT from the 
original project name. The original project name includes, but is not limited to:

1. Repository name (e.g., "DryFishLib" → "WetFishLib" ✓ or "DRYFISH" ✗)
2. Package/Namespace name (e.g., "com.dryfish.core" → "com.wetfish.core" ✓)
3. Binary/Executable name (e.g., "dryfish-cli" → "wetfish-cli" ✓)
4. Display name (e.g., "DryFish Library" → "WetFish Library" ✓)
5. Logo and branding elements (must be visually distinct)
6. Any marketing terms used to identify the software
7. Domain names and URLs associated with the project
8. Social media handles (Twitter, GitHub, etc.)

"Clearly different" means:
- Different root words (e.g., "Fish" → "Shark")
- Different conceptual branding (e.g., "Dry" → "Wet")
- Visually distinct (not just changing case, spacing, or punctuation)

The following are considered VIOLATIONS of this section:
- Changing only case: "DryFishLib" → "dryfishlib" or "DRYFISHLIB"
- Adding only punctuation: "DryFishLib" → "Dry-Fish-Lib" or "DryFish.Lib"
- Adding only numbers: "DryFishLib" → "DryFishLib2" or "DryFishLib2024"
- Changing only spacing: "DryFishLib" → "Dry Fish Lib"
- Using abbreviations that clearly refer to the original: "DryFishLib" → "DFL" or "DFLib"
- Adding prefixes/suffixes that don't change the core identity: "DryFishLib" → "SuperDryFishLib" or "DryFishLibPro"

The following are considered COMPLIANT with this section:
- Different root word: "DryFishLib" → "WetFishLib" or "AquaLib"
- Completely different name: "DryFishLib" → "SuperLogger" or "DataProcessor"
- Different branding concept: "DryFishLib" → "BlueOcean" or "CrystalCore"

EXCEPTION: If you are using the Software as a LIBRARY, PACKAGE, OR DEPENDENCY
within your own project (whether modified or unmodified), you are NOT required
to rename the library's internal package name, class names, or namespace.
The original package name (e.g., com.dryfish.core) may remain unchanged.
However, if you distribute the library itself as a separate product, you MUST
rename the distribution name (e.g., JAR filename, npm package name, PyPI package name).

